1
00:00:11,167 --> 00:00:12,500
<i> Lucas!</i>

2
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:13,633
<i> Argh!</i>

3
00:00:15,433 --> 00:00:16,567
<i> Bro!</i>

4
00:00:18,133 --> 00:00:22,733
<i> Bro! Bro!</i>

5
00:00:23,567 --> 00:00:28,000
<i>Call Lieutenant Areza.
Surrender me to him.</i>

6
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:30,267
<i> Boss, this is Areza's phone.</i>

7
00:00:30,267 --> 00:00:33,333
<i>- Lieutenant Areza...
- Sir?</i>

8
00:00:33,333 --> 00:00:34,933
<i> My wife is with me.</i>

9
00:00:35,633 --> 00:00:39,500
<i>We're located
at 25 Kings Road, Alicante.</i>

10
00:00:39,500 --> 00:00:41,300
<i>Leni's with me now.
What's the plan?</i>

11
00:00:42,267 --> 00:00:44,167
<i> Pa! Where are you?</i>

12
00:00:44,167 --> 00:00:46,000
<i> Let's stop this, Pa...</i>

13
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:47,300
<i> ...before we all die.</i>

14
00:00:47,300 --> 00:00:49,800
<i>We're almost there, my dear.
This is the last mission.</i>

15
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:52,200
<i> To finally find your sister.</i>

16
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:55,633
<i>Magnus knows where she is.
I'll pressure him.</i>

17
00:00:55,633 --> 00:00:56,800
<i> Ma, let's go.</i>

18
00:00:56,800 --> 00:00:59,533
<i>Don't go there. We won't gain
anything from it.</i>

19
00:00:59,533 --> 00:01:03,433
<i>Let's wait for the police.
I want to be sure.</i>

20
00:01:03,433 --> 00:01:07,100
<i>I want to see them
arresting Greta.</i>

21
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:08,133
<i> They're here.</i>

22
00:01:16,500 --> 00:01:23,700
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

23
00:01:26,833 --> 00:01:28,033
They're here.

24
00:01:34,367 --> 00:01:35,467
[EMIL] Ugh...

25
00:01:35,467 --> 00:01:42,333
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

26
00:01:58,200 --> 00:02:00,767
[REPORTER]<i> The mastermind
</i>behind the La Playa Roja siege,

27
00:02:00,767 --> 00:02:04,200
<i>Emil Padua, escaped
after an encounter</i>

28
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:07,067
<i>that resulted in the death
of Police Lt. Marlon Areza</i>

29
00:02:07,067 --> 00:02:08,500
<i> and his team.</i>

30
00:02:08,500 --> 00:02:10,367
<i>It should be noted
that Lieutenant Areza</i>

31
00:02:10,367 --> 00:02:12,733
led the rescue of the hostages.

32
00:02:13,733 --> 00:02:16,533
- Is it still far?
- About 30 minutes.

33
00:02:17,900 --> 00:02:19,400
Good thing you came up
with the idea

34
00:02:19,400 --> 00:02:22,467
to put a tracker
on the car Olsen borrowed.

35
00:02:22,467 --> 00:02:24,267
[VOICE PROMPT] Please try
again later.

36
00:02:24,267 --> 00:02:26,200
They cannot be reached.

37
00:02:26,200 --> 00:02:28,467
Macky, why did they even borrow
a car from you?

38
00:02:28,467 --> 00:02:29,867
Where did they say
they were going?

39
00:02:30,733 --> 00:02:31,900
We'll find out soon.

40
00:02:31,900 --> 00:02:33,767
[VOICE PROMPT] The subscriber
cannot be reached.

41
00:02:33,767 --> 00:02:35,600
<i>- Please try again later.
- I can't reach Liam, too.</i>

42
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:39,533
Fin, do you think
he's with Olsen?

43
00:02:41,767 --> 00:02:45,867
There's a problem again.
Something tells me this is bad.

44
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:49,800
Macky, why did you run away
from your bodyguards?

45
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:51,300
We don't have backup now!

46
00:02:51,300 --> 00:02:52,600
Dad tightened security again...

47
00:02:53,433 --> 00:02:55,733
...when he found
out Emil Padua escaped.

48
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:58,667
We should report this
to the police!

49
00:02:58,667 --> 00:02:59,800
What will you report?

50
00:03:00,933 --> 00:03:03,833
We're not sure
if Olsen is in danger.

51
00:03:03,833 --> 00:03:06,633
- Or even Liam.
- Ivan.

52
00:03:06,633 --> 00:03:09,567
That's why we're here
to make sure they're okay.

53
00:03:10,900 --> 00:03:12,800
Macky, can't this go
any faster?

54
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:13,900
Wait.

55
00:03:13,900 --> 00:03:17,567
[STIRRING MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

56
00:03:17,567 --> 00:03:24,467
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

57
00:04:01,733 --> 00:04:08,667
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

58
00:04:23,667 --> 00:04:30,633
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

59
00:04:45,700 --> 00:04:52,667
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

60
00:04:57,867 --> 00:05:00,400
- Magnus...
- Greta.

61
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:04,267
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

62
00:05:04,300 --> 00:05:05,567
[GRETA BREATHES DEEPLY]

63
00:05:06,733 --> 00:05:07,700
Son...

64
00:05:13,300 --> 00:05:15,900
[LIAM] I'll visit. Always.

65
00:05:15,900 --> 00:05:20,567
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

66
00:05:20,567 --> 00:05:22,300
[DOOR THUDS, SLAMS]

67
00:05:22,300 --> 00:05:29,267
[MUSIC TURNS TENSE]

68
00:05:39,767 --> 00:05:46,733
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

69
00:05:52,333 --> 00:05:58,733
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

70
00:06:04,267 --> 00:06:07,133
You're apparently
my real boss, Ma'am Greta.

71
00:06:12,033 --> 00:06:13,733
You should've told me.

72
00:06:14,967 --> 00:06:16,500
What else are you doing here?

73
00:06:17,867 --> 00:06:19,433
You already got the money.

74
00:06:19,433 --> 00:06:21,800
Your daughter, Leni,
is with you.

75
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:29,733
- What else?
- I still have one mission.

76
00:06:31,100 --> 00:06:35,033
The real reason
why I said yes to all of this.

77
00:06:35,033 --> 00:06:40,133
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

78
00:06:40,133 --> 00:06:42,033
My daughter, Ayen.

79
00:06:42,067 --> 00:06:49,033
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

80
00:06:54,900 --> 00:06:57,800
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

81
00:06:57,800 --> 00:06:59,467
<i> What are you doing here?</i>

82
00:07:02,567 --> 00:07:03,867
<i> How did you get in?</i>

83
00:07:08,033 --> 00:07:09,267
<i> Ah!</i>

84
00:07:14,433 --> 00:07:15,467
<i> Is that all?</i>

85
00:07:18,267 --> 00:07:20,067
<i> Go ahead, Greta.</i>

86
00:07:20,067 --> 00:07:21,800
<i>Destroy everything
you want to destroy.</i>

87
00:07:24,100 --> 00:07:26,067
<i>Magnus will just replace those
with new ones.</i>

88
00:07:27,567 --> 00:07:29,867
<i>Everything can be replaced
with something new.</i>

89
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:33,500
<i> Even you.</i>

90
00:07:33,500 --> 00:07:37,433
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

91
00:07:37,433 --> 00:07:39,233
<i> Do you really know Magnus?</i>

92
00:07:40,333 --> 00:07:42,933
<i>My husband will also
get tired of you.</i>

93
00:07:42,933 --> 00:07:44,533
<i> He will replace you as well.</i>

94
00:07:44,533 --> 00:07:46,900
<i>And in the end,
he'll come back to me.</i>

95
00:07:48,567 --> 00:07:50,367
<i> Really?</i>

96
00:07:53,433 --> 00:07:56,367
<i>If that's the case, why are
you wasting your time on me?</i>

97
00:07:59,033 --> 00:08:01,467
- [ENVELOPE THUDS]
- [PAPERS RUSTLING]

98
00:08:01,467 --> 00:08:04,433
<i>Because my husband wasn't
the only thing you stole.</i>

99
00:08:04,433 --> 00:08:09,633
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

100
00:08:09,633 --> 00:08:10,933
[AYEN SCOFFS]

101
00:08:13,567 --> 00:08:15,100
<i> My gosh, Greta...</i>

102
00:08:16,033 --> 00:08:16,967
[PAPERS RUSTLING]

103
00:08:16,967 --> 00:08:18,533
<i>Before Magnus and I
became a couple,</i>

104
00:08:18,533 --> 00:08:22,000
<i>didn't you conspire with me to
steal money from your company?</i>

105
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:26,400
<i>You think you're the only one
who'll benefit from that?</i>

106
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:29,433
<i> The money that I took...</i>

107
00:08:30,667 --> 00:08:32,300
<i> That's my service fee...</i>

108
00:08:33,133 --> 00:08:36,000
<i>...for getting
your finances flowing</i>

109
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:38,367
<i>to sustain
all your gambling!</i>

110
00:08:39,333 --> 00:08:40,933
<i> You'll pay for this!</i>

111
00:08:42,133 --> 00:08:43,300
<i> Try me.</i>

112
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:47,467
<i>Let's see if Magnus
will believe you.</i>

113
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:50,400
<i> Are you blackmailing me?</i>

114
00:08:51,300 --> 00:08:52,500
[GRETA SCOFFS]

115
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:56,467
<i> I'll turn the tables on you,</i>

116
00:08:56,500 --> 00:08:59,000
<i> and point you as the thief.</i>

117
00:09:00,133 --> 00:09:02,000
<i> That's if he'll believe you.</i>

118
00:09:03,667 --> 00:09:04,633
[AYEN SCOFFS]

119
00:09:06,633 --> 00:09:09,000
<i> Greta, Magnus will believe me.</i>

120
00:09:10,333 --> 00:09:14,500
<i>Especially now that he knows
he'll be a father again soon.</i>

121
00:09:14,500 --> 00:09:19,533
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

122
00:09:19,533 --> 00:09:20,600
<i> Yes, Greta.</i>

123
00:09:21,667 --> 00:09:22,967
<i> I'm pregnant.</i>

124
00:09:23,933 --> 00:09:25,400
<i> And Magnus is the father.</i>

125
00:09:27,033 --> 00:09:28,133
[SLAP LANDS]

126
00:09:30,033 --> 00:09:31,133
- [AYEN]<i> Argh!
</i>- [GRETA] Ugh!

127
00:09:33,033 --> 00:09:35,533
<i>- You witch!
- Argh!</i>

128
00:09:37,967 --> 00:09:38,967
<i> Ugh.</i>

129
00:09:50,533 --> 00:09:51,933
Tell me.

130
00:09:52,567 --> 00:09:54,233
Where is Ayen?

131
00:09:54,233 --> 00:10:01,200
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

132
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:08,200
We don't know
where Ayen is.

133
00:10:10,267 --> 00:10:13,733
Because of you, my daughter
and I had a fight.

134
00:10:17,033 --> 00:10:18,167
<i> What's that?</i>

135
00:10:19,367 --> 00:10:21,367
<i>- Who did that?
- This is nothing, Pa.</i>

136
00:10:23,367 --> 00:10:25,367
<i> Is Magnus hurting you?</i>

137
00:10:27,533 --> 00:10:29,233
<i> No, Pa.</i>

138
00:10:29,233 --> 00:10:30,733
<i>How many times
has that happened?</i>

139
00:10:35,133 --> 00:10:37,767
<i>- Huh?
- Pa, Magnus doesn't hurt me.</i>

140
00:10:39,467 --> 00:10:41,200
<i> He can't do that to me.</i>

141
00:10:42,567 --> 00:10:44,233
Don't cover up for him anymore.

142
00:10:46,133 --> 00:10:48,367
<i> If he did that once...</i>

143
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:50,600
<i> He could do it again.</i>

144
00:10:53,467 --> 00:10:55,567
Didn't I tell you to leave him?

145
00:10:55,567 --> 00:10:56,600
<i> Pa...</i>

146
00:10:58,300 --> 00:10:59,367
<i> Pa.</i>

147
00:11:01,533 --> 00:11:03,367
<i> Magnus and I love each other.</i>

148
00:11:05,133 --> 00:11:07,000
<i>His family already knows
about it.</i>

149
00:11:08,167 --> 00:11:09,400
I told her...

150
00:11:10,167 --> 00:11:14,200
"Magnus will just trick you.
He'll leave you."

151
00:11:15,667 --> 00:11:17,067
That's right, isn't it?!

152
00:11:19,567 --> 00:11:22,067
I should have sympathized
with my daughter,

153
00:11:22,067 --> 00:11:23,767
should have understood her.

154
00:11:23,767 --> 00:11:25,467
But she got angry at me.

155
00:11:26,667 --> 00:11:29,133
I even blamed her
for her sins.

156
00:11:30,167 --> 00:11:31,800
And that was the last...

157
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:34,567
That was the last time
we saw each other.

158
00:11:34,567 --> 00:11:38,467
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

159
00:11:38,467 --> 00:11:41,633
Now, tell me. Where is Ayen?!

160
00:11:44,333 --> 00:11:46,167
Where's my daughter?!

161
00:11:46,167 --> 00:11:49,600
- We don't know where Ayen is.
- No?

162
00:11:51,500 --> 00:11:52,667
[RAPID GUNFIRE]

163
00:11:54,500 --> 00:11:55,700
- [MAGNUS] Liam!
- [LIAM] Argh!

164
00:11:55,700 --> 00:11:57,133
- [MAGNUS] Liam!
- [GRETA] Son!

165
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:03,133
The next bullet...

166
00:12:03,133 --> 00:12:04,667
...won't miss.

167
00:12:04,667 --> 00:12:07,200
I'll bury it
in your son's chest!

168
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:08,267
Stop it!

169
00:12:10,300 --> 00:12:11,567
- Where?!
- [MAGNUS] Sorry, sorry!

170
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,433
Okay, okay. Sorry, sorry.

171
00:12:16,833 --> 00:12:18,200
I'll tell you.

172
00:12:20,833 --> 00:12:23,400
- I'll tell you.
- Ayen's gone!

173
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:25,300
- She's dead!
- Greta! No!

174
00:12:25,300 --> 00:12:29,867
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

175
00:12:29,867 --> 00:12:30,800
What?!

176
00:12:40,700 --> 00:12:41,667
What?!

177
00:12:41,667 --> 00:12:48,033
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

178
00:12:49,500 --> 00:12:54,533
[AYEN BREATHING LABORIOUSLY]

179
00:12:57,067 --> 00:12:58,600
[AYEN CRYING]

180
00:12:58,600 --> 00:12:59,867
<i> You witch!</i>

181
00:13:01,033 --> 00:13:02,600
<i>- You witch!
- [KNIFE SWISHING]</i>

182
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:04,067
- [AYEN]<i> Argh!
</i>- [GRETA] Ahh!

183
00:13:04,900 --> 00:13:07,833
<i>- Ah! Ah! Ah!
- Argh!</i>

184
00:13:07,833 --> 00:13:14,733
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

185
00:13:14,733 --> 00:13:18,033
<i>- Argh! Ugh... Ugh...
- Ugh...</i>

186
00:13:19,733 --> 00:13:20,733
<i>- Ah!
- Ah!</i>

187
00:13:20,733 --> 00:13:21,700
[KNIFE SWISHING]

188
00:13:23,767 --> 00:13:25,100
[GRETA BREATHING HEAVILY]

189
00:13:26,033 --> 00:13:27,833
- [AYEN GRUNTS]
- [BODY THUDS]

190
00:13:29,967 --> 00:13:35,900
[AYEN BREATHING LABORIOUSLY]

191
00:13:48,967 --> 00:13:49,967
[DOOR KNOB CLICKS]

192
00:13:49,967 --> 00:13:56,067
[GRETA CRYING]

193
00:13:56,100 --> 00:13:57,200
<i> What happened?</i>

194
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:00,900
<i>- What happened?
- I didn't mean it.</i>

195
00:14:01,967 --> 00:14:05,600
<i>I didn't mean it, Magnus.
Magnus...</i>

196
00:14:06,600 --> 00:14:13,533
[GRETA CRYING]

197
00:14:17,133 --> 00:14:20,100
<i> I just defended myself.</i>

198
00:14:20,100 --> 00:14:21,067
<i> I-- I--</i>

199
00:14:22,067 --> 00:14:24,800
<i> I didn't mean it.</i>

200
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:31,767
[GRETA CRYING]

201
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:36,067
<i> Okay... Okay. Okay.</i>

202
00:14:37,667 --> 00:14:38,767
<i> Okay.</i>

203
00:14:38,767 --> 00:14:41,167
[GRETA CRYING]

204
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:44,500
I was just defending
myself, Emil.

205
00:14:47,167 --> 00:14:50,667
[GRETA] I just defended myself.
She was so furious.

206
00:14:50,667 --> 00:14:53,333
I pushed her.
She miscarried.

207
00:14:53,333 --> 00:14:55,000
She was going to kill me!

208
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:57,800
I didn't mean it.
I didn't mean it!

209
00:15:00,700 --> 00:15:02,067
My daughter was pregnant?

210
00:15:03,067 --> 00:15:05,133
You didn't just kill
my daughter,

211
00:15:05,133 --> 00:15:06,933
but my grandchild, too!

212
00:15:08,033 --> 00:15:09,033
Ma...

213
00:15:11,667 --> 00:15:12,800
[MAGNUS] No, no, Greta.

214
00:15:12,800 --> 00:15:14,733
- Emil. Emil.
- [MAGNUS] Greta.

215
00:15:14,733 --> 00:15:17,167
[GRETA] It's my fault!
It's all my fault!

216
00:15:17,167 --> 00:15:18,700
All mine!

217
00:15:19,567 --> 00:15:21,700
Don't get them involved
in this.

218
00:15:21,700 --> 00:15:23,233
Wendy, Olsen, Magnus,

219
00:15:23,233 --> 00:15:27,033
especially my son, Emil.
Especially my son.

220
00:15:27,033 --> 00:15:28,167
- [GRETA] Ah!
- [LIAM] Ma!

221
00:15:29,300 --> 00:15:30,333
[GRETA CRYING]

222
00:15:30,333 --> 00:15:32,000
That's enough! That's enough.

223
00:15:36,267 --> 00:15:38,033
If what you're saying
is true...

224
00:15:39,767 --> 00:15:41,767
Where's my daughter's body?!

225
00:15:41,767 --> 00:15:46,267
[EMIL CRYING]

226
00:15:46,267 --> 00:15:47,733
Where?!

227
00:15:47,733 --> 00:15:49,700
[EMIL CRYING]

228
00:15:49,700 --> 00:15:50,900
I'll show you.

229
00:15:53,033 --> 00:15:55,167
[EMIL SOBBING]

230
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:05,700
[EMIL SOBBING]

231
00:16:07,233 --> 00:16:12,700
[EMIL SOBBING ANGRILY]

232
00:16:14,867 --> 00:16:15,900
[SHOVEL THUMPS]

233
00:16:17,533 --> 00:16:20,033
[SHOVELS THUMP]

234
00:16:28,033 --> 00:16:29,200
<i> Don't worry.</i>

235
00:16:30,733 --> 00:16:32,067
<i> I will handle this.</i>

236
00:16:34,233 --> 00:16:35,700
<i> Okay? I promise you.</i>

237
00:16:36,967 --> 00:16:38,067
<i> I'll fix this.</i>

238
00:16:39,567 --> 00:16:42,167
<i> Don't worry. Don't worry.</i>

239
00:16:45,233 --> 00:16:52,200
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

240
00:16:59,233 --> 00:17:00,233
[CAR TRUNK CLICKS]

241
00:17:00,233 --> 00:17:07,133
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

242
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:29,133
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

243
00:17:37,767 --> 00:17:44,667
[MUSIC TURNS SOMBER]

244
00:17:59,733 --> 00:18:06,700
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

245
00:18:19,367 --> 00:18:21,733
[SHOVELS THUMP]

246
00:18:21,767 --> 00:18:23,767
I'm begging you, Emil.

247
00:18:23,767 --> 00:18:25,833
They have nothing
to do with this.

248
00:18:25,833 --> 00:18:27,100
All of you...

249
00:18:27,100 --> 00:18:29,633
...had something to do with
what happened to my daughter.

250
00:18:30,733 --> 00:18:32,033
[RAPID GUNFIRE]

251
00:18:32,033 --> 00:18:33,067
Keep digging!

252
00:18:35,767 --> 00:18:37,067
[SHOVELS THUMP]

253
00:18:38,900 --> 00:18:40,067
[LIAM] Argh...

254
00:18:40,067 --> 00:18:41,367
[SHOVEL THUMPS]

255
00:18:41,367 --> 00:18:44,700
[SHOVEL CLINKS]

256
00:18:44,700 --> 00:18:51,667
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

257
00:19:03,800 --> 00:19:05,067
<i> Is he really my son?</i>

258
00:19:05,067 --> 00:19:06,300
<i> Don't do this to our son.</i>

259
00:19:06,300 --> 00:19:09,800
<i>Why are we paying
for the sins of others?</i>

260
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:11,267
<i> I'm Greta's victim, too!</i>

261
00:19:12,133 --> 00:19:14,233
<i>Don't tell me
we're going on their side?</i>

262
00:19:14,233 --> 00:19:16,267
Olsen, who really is our enemy?

263
00:19:16,267 --> 00:19:20,433
<i>The Rojas who take advantage
of the poor and the weak?</i>

264
00:19:20,433 --> 00:19:24,400
<i>Or them, who were taken
advantage just like us?</i>

265
00:19:24,400 --> 00:19:26,800
<i> The Rojas all used us!</i>

266
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:28,900
<i>Will you still be
on their side?</i>

267
00:19:28,933 --> 00:19:29,933
<i> Son!</i>

268
00:19:34,067 --> 00:19:35,267
<i> Stay here.</i>

269
00:19:35,967 --> 00:19:38,433
<i>Gwen, wait. Gwen,
where's my dad? Gwen!</i>

270
00:19:48,167 --> 00:19:52,067
<i>- You're really like your mom.
- What? I'm also chatty?</i>

271
00:19:52,067 --> 00:19:54,933
<i>You're caring, too.
And you look so much like her.</i>

272
00:20:00,900 --> 00:20:02,267
<i> Ahh! Ah!</i>

273
00:20:09,500 --> 00:20:12,167
<i>You'll be together
until death!</i>
